Key Match Events: Donte DiVincenzo scored 26 points to lead the Timberwolves to a 112-110 victory over the Spurs
Rudy Gobert had 17 points and 15 rebounds for the Timberwolves
Julius Randle made a driving layup against Wembanyama that was initially whistled for an offensive foul but was allowed to stand, which proved to be a key moment in the game
Miscellaneous Highlights: Anthony Edwards, who was fined $100,000 for continued use of profanity in postgame media comments, was held to 14 points, 11 below his season average
Others: The Spurs found a wide-open Jeremy Sochan for a potential game-winning three-pointer but he came up short
Harrison Barnes had 24 points, Devin Vassell had 22 and Chris Paul dished out 14 assists for the Spurs
Minnesota survived a brutal shooting night from 3-point range, making just 11 of 44 attempts
